title: Buckle, "Snake-form belt buckle", ca. 1890
description: Buckle in two parts: each part is triangular in shape and is composed of entwined snakees (six snakes in each part); bodies studded wtih diamons paste, heads, with emerald and ruby paste.  Buckle is mounted on a pad of white satin, one stone missing.

tombstone.epitaph:
Buckle, "Snake-form belt buckle", ca. 1890.
ca. 1890. Silver gilt, glass. Gift of Anonymous Donor. 1942-69-2-a,b.
